diggings
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a goldfield usu. where surface or alluvial mining in registered claims is being carried out (1851-1853 usu. with reference to Australia or California, often in quotation marks, and prefixed with gold).
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Geology
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Early spg (or var. form) diggins, occas. digins. [Spec. use of digging(s) applied to a goldfield in California, then Australia and NZ.] [1853 Adams Spring Canterbury Settlement 56-57 diggins.] Common pronunciation was `diggins' [check] (Griffiths Collection). 1. [AND 1851.]  (Collect. pl. or pl. regarded as a sg., the diggings.)
