Date: 10/12/1852
Source: NZ Government Gazette
Author:
Vol / Page: V/30/183
Edition:
Quote: ... the annexed tabular report of the work at this Gold-field since my arrival. ... wherever I and the Messrs. Ring have `prospected'  on the Kapanga ..., we have found gold, and that the greatest number of flakes in the prospecting dish, appeared upon washing some earth yesterday at a bar about half a mile lower down the stream ...; and below all the present diggings.
Notes: (Heaphy's Report) Kapanga River Diggings,/ Coromandel harbour,/ 4th November, 1852.

