Date: 7/1/1863
Source: Journal and Letters (Walker)
Author: WALKER
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: The diggings [at Dunstan] extend 80 miles one way and fifteen another. If you want to boil a pot you have to hunt about for dead `Wild Irishmen' a nasty prickly little shrub. The high lands abounded with `Spaniards' I suppose from their cut-throat propensities. A kind of very thick grass, grows in a little lump.
Notes:

